metadata.name: redblack #47
metadata.description: I've had a busy few months lately, but I still love making art! I've chosen an abstract art project as my comeback. I'm just obsessed with simple shapes, simple colors, and varying thickness levels when it comes to lines and rectangles. I stuck to a simple color palette for all the pieces. The variation is in the mix of black and red blocks, the combination of sizes, and the vertical boundary. Please enjoy, I hope you get some wonderful outputs, I know I did during all my testing :D

metadata.name: Wild Matrix #325
metadata.description:
Wild Matrix art project are just patterns, all kind, created using triangles, rectangles, squares and a lot of colors :)

If you like patterns -> be wild, mint free a Wild Matrix!

25% of secondary sales goes to Proceesing Foundation (let's encourage and sustain generative art) | 25% of secondary sales goes to SavePakistan (let's help people in need). 

I would kindly appreciate a share, a follow of my Twitter or just make your mint know to others if you like it.

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #258
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect “fx(haish) - the Generator”
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your “fx(haish) - The AI City” based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.
